<TITLE> JMB operative sentenced to death for killing convert </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 20 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court Monday sentenced Jamaatul Mujahideen Bangladesh leader Salahuddin to hang for murdering Hridoy Roy, who had converted to Christianity from Islam. Judge Md Israil Hossain of the Speedy Trial Tribunal Dhaka-4 in the verdict however cleared Amir Khan and Sharif Monwar Shiplu of the charges of the murder that took place in Jamalpur in 2003. Salahuddin was present in court. After the sentencing, he said he did what he thought was right. The tribunal had also sentenced Salahuddin, accused in 19 cases, to death by hanging in the Gani Gomes killing case. He is awaiting verdicts in 17 criminal cases. According to case details, Salahuddin slaughtered Hridoy, a Christian and tenant of Tahera Khatun in Sanakoir village under Sharishabari upazila in Jamalpur on April 23, 2003. He accused Hridoy of converting to Christianity and trying to convert others to the same religion. "He (Salahuddin) entered his house and killed him," said Khatun, who filed a case with Sharishabari Police Station. Police pressed charges against Salahuddin nicknamed Salehin, Amir and Shiplu and the court examined 15 witnesses during trial. bdnew
